result.name: Nebraska Steak House Hong Kong

reviews.text: This restaurant is cozy, family, couples-oriented and a little pricey. However, the steak was well prepared. The service was over the roof. Love it. I will eat there again. Be ready to spend $100 to $200 Canadian.

After numerous glowing reviews from a co-worker we decided to try Half-Price Tomahawk Monday. Medium-rare and gorgeous our Tomahawk arrived (maybe just over but for a 1.7kg raw hunk of meat they did great!) and we dove in. 
The meat was great (don't dare accept the toppings, a pinch of salt and a nice soft roasted glove of garlic is all you need. Split well between two of us, though I'd suggest staying away from the asparagus unless you like it limp and steamed. Personally I'd prefer a pinch of salt and pepper in a quick roll of olive oil then a toss on a hot grill or skillet, but to each their own.

We visited on Tuesday night when there was the 50% off promotion on the tomahawk. We also ordered a few appetizers, salad and onion soup.

We were first given some garlic bread. Very delicious and crispy! 

The onion soup comes with a generous amount of cheese, but the stock was not as flavorful as it looks. 

The avacado salad consisted of avocado and lettuce. The dressing is olive oil and balsamic vinegar. I didn't know other dishes would come with some green. I wouldn't order extra salad if I knew the green we would get. 

Crab cake was very delicious, but the portion is smaller than what I have expected. Worth a try but expect it to be smaller size.

The tomahawk itself worth a visit to this restaurant. We ordered medium, and it was skillfully cooked to perfection. Tasted very well.  There are 3 of us and we still couldn't finish 1.4kg. We ordered fries and mashed potato as side dish. 

With the promotion, the price is very reasonable. Would visit again. Next time we will order fewer appetizers so we have more room for steak and desserts.
Perfect meat,good service, price is right
Nice sirloin with chewy texture. The atmosphere is not bad.
